Package org.cesecore.certificates.certificate

Interface CertificateStoreSession

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    CertificateStoreSessionLocal, CertificateStoreSessionRemote
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CertificateStoreSessionBean
    public interface CertificateStoreSession
    Interface for certificate store operations Stores certificate in the local database using Certificate JPA Beans. IMPORTANT: No publishing to publishersession from setRevokeStatus
    Version:
    $Id: CertificateStoreSession.java 29011 2018-05-23 13:41:10Z jekaterina_b_helmes $

    • Method Detail

      • listAllCertificates

        Collection<String> listAllCertificates​(String issuerdn)
        Lists fingerprint (primary key) of ALL certificates in the database. NOTE: Caution should be taken with this method as execution may be very heavy indeed if many certificates exist in the database (imagine what happens if there are millions of certificates in the DB!). Should only be used for testing purposes.
        Parameters:
        issuerdn - the dn of the certificates issuer.
        Returns:
        Collection of fingerprints, i.e. Strings

      • listRevokedCertInfo

        Collection<RevokedCertInfo> listRevokedCertInfo​(String issuerdn,
                                                long lastbasecrldate)
        Lists RevokedCertInfo of ALL revoked certificates (status = CertificateConstants.CERT_REVOKED) in the database from a certain issuer. NOTE: Caution should be taken with this method as execution may be very heavy indeed if many certificates exist in the database (imagine what happens if there are millions of certificates in the DB!). Should only be used for testing purposes.
        Parameters:
        issuerdn - the dn of the certificates issuer.
        lastbasecrldate - a date (Date.getTime()) of last base CRL or -1 for a complete CRL
        Returns:
        Collection of RevokedCertInfo, reverse ordered by expireDate where last expireDate is first in array.

        Collection<Certificate> findCertificatesByIssuerAndSernos​(String issuerDN,
                                                          Collection<BigInteger> sernos)
        The method retrieves all certificates from a specific issuer which are identified by list of serial numbers. The collection will be empty if the issuerDN is null/empty or the collection of serial numbers is empty.

        issuerDN - the subjectDN of a CA certificate
        sernos - a collection of certificate serialnumbers
        Returns:
        Collection a list of certificates; never null

      • findLatestX509CertificateBySubject

        X509Certificate findLatestX509CertificateBySubject​(String subjectDN)
        Find the latest published X509Certificate matching the given subject DN. Note that this method does not check if the returned certificate was issued by a rollover CA.
        Parameters:
        subjectDN - The subject DN to match.
        Returns:
        the sought result, or null if none exists.

      • findLatestX509CertificateBySubject

        X509Certificate findLatestX509CertificateBySubject​(String subjectDN,
                                                   X509Certificate rolloverCA,
                                                   boolean findRollover)
        Find the latest published X509Certificate matching the given subject DN. This method can search for normal or rollover certificates.
        Parameters:
        subjectDN - The subject DN to match.
        rolloverCA - The rollover certificate of the issuing CA, or null to not check if issued by a rollover certificate.
        findRollover - Whether a rollover or normal certificate should be returned.
        Returns:
        the sought result, or null if none exists.

      • getCertificateDataByUsername

        List<CertificateDataWrapper> getCertificateDataByUsername​(String username,
                                                          boolean excludeExpired,
                                                          List<Integer> excludedStatuses)
        Finds certificate(s) with meta data for a given username.
        Parameters:
        username - the username of the certificate(s) that will be retrieved
        excludeExpired - true if expired certificates should be excluded
        excludedStatuses - a list of statuses to exclude in the query or null to return all
        Returns:
        List of wrapped CertificateData and Base64CertData ordered by expire date, with last expire date first, or empty list if none found.

      • findCertificatesByUsernameAndStatus

        Collection<Certificate> findCertificatesByUsernameAndStatus​(String username,
                                                            int status)
        Finds certificate(s) for a given username and status.
        Parameters:
        username - the username of the certificate(s) that will be retrieved
        status - the status from the CertificateConstants.CERT_ constants
        Returns:
        Collection of Certificates ordered by expire date, with last expire date first, or empty list if user can not be found

      • findCertificatesByUsernameAndStatusAfterExpireDate

        Collection<Certificate> findCertificatesByUsernameAndStatusAfterExpireDate​(String username,
                                                                           int status,
                                                                           long afterExpireDate)
        Finds certificate(s) for a given username and status if the expireDate is after the provided one.
        Parameters:
        username - the username of the certificate(s) that will be retrieved
        status - the status from the CertificateConstants.CERT_ constants
        afterExpireDate - only return entries that has an expireDate larger than or equal to this one
        Returns:
        Collection of Certificates ordered by expire date, with last expire date first, or empty list if user can not be found

      • getCertificateInfo

        CertificateInfo getCertificateInfo​(String fingerprint)
        Gets certificate info, which is basically all fields except the certificate itself. Note: this method should not be used within a transaction where the reading of this info might depend on something stored earlier in the transaction. This is because this method uses direct SQL.
        Parameters:
        fingerprint - FP
        Returns:
        CertificateInfo or null if certificate does not exist.

      • findCertificateByFingerprint

        Certificate findCertificateByFingerprint​(String fingerprint)
        Finds a certificate based on fingerprint. You can get fingerprint by for example "String fingerprint = CertTools.getFingerprintAsString(certificate);"
        Parameters:
        fingerprint - FP
        Returns:
        Certificate or null if it can not be found.

      • findCertificatesByType

        Collection<CertificateWrapper> findCertificatesByType​(int type,
                                                      String issuerDN)
        Lists all active (status = 20) certificates of a specific type and if given from a specific issuer.
        Parameters:
        issuerDN - get all certificates issued by a specific issuer. If null or empty return certificates regardless of the issuer.
        type - CERTTYPE_* types from CertificateConstants
        Returns:
        Collection of Certificate, never null
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - when admin is null or type is not one or more of of SecConst.CERTTYPE_SUBCA, SecConst.CERTTYPE_ENDENTITY, SecConst.CERTTYPE_ROOTCA

      • getCertificateChain

        List<Certificate> getCertificateChain​(CertificateInfo certinfo)
        Recursively finds the certificate chain for the given certificate.
        Parameters:
        certinfo - Certificate to start from, usually a leaf certificate.
        Returns:
        List containing certificate chain, starting with the given certificate.

      • revokeAllCertByCA

        void revokeAllCertByCA​(AuthenticationToken admin,
                       String issuerdn,
                       int reason)
                throws AuthorizationDeniedException
        Method revoking all certificates generated by the specified issuerdn. Sets revocationDate to current time. Should only be called by when a CA is about to be revoked.
        Parameters:
        admin - the administrator performing the event.
        issuerdn - the dn of CA about to be revoked
        reason - the reason of revocation.
        Throws:
        AuthorizationDeniedException - Access denied

      • isRevoked

        boolean isRevoked​(String issuerDN,
                  BigInteger serno)
        Checks if a certificate is revoked.
        Parameters:
        issuerDN - the DN of the issuer.
        serno - the serialnumber of the certificate that will be checked
        Returns:
        true if the certificate is revoked or can not be found in the database, false if it exists and is not revoked.

      • getStatus

        CertificateStatus getStatus​(String issuerDN,
                            BigInteger serno)
        Get certificate status fast.
        Parameters:
        issuerDN - Issuer DN
        serno - Serial No.
        Returns:
        CertificateStatus status of the certificate, never null, CertificateStatus.NOT_AVAILABLE if the certificate is not found.

      • getCertificateAndStatus

        CertificateStatusHolder getCertificateAndStatus​(String issuerDN,
                                                BigInteger serno)
        Performs the same operation as getStatus, but returns a richer object which also contains the certificate, in order to save on database lookups when both objects are required. Issuer + serial number are always unique.
        Parameters:
        issuerDN - the issuer of the sought certificate
        serno - the serial number of the sought certificate
        Returns:
        a CertificateStatusHolder object containing the status and the sought certificate.

      • setStatus

        boolean setStatus​(AuthenticationToken admin,
                  String fingerprint,
                  int status)
           throws AuthorizationDeniedException
        Update the status of a cert in the database.
        Parameters:
        admin - Auth token
        fingerprint - FP
        status - one of CertificateConstants.CERT_...
        Returns:
        true if the status was updated, false if not, for example if the certificate did not exist
        Throws:
        AuthorizationDeniedException - Access Denied
